# S01-T02: Feature-Driven Directory Architecture

## Objective
Create the canonical feature-driven directory structure.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Directory structure created:
  ```
  src/
    app/              # App shell, providers, router, global error boundary
      App.tsx
      providers.tsx
      router.tsx
    features/
      video/          # EPIC 2 — Camera/video pipeline
      hud/            # EPIC 3 — HUD rendering
      telemetry/      # EPIC 5 — Realtime telemetry
      touch/          # EPIC 6 — Touch gestures
      debug/          # EPIC 8 — Debug tooling
    entities/
      telemetry/      # TelemetryData type, constants
      stream/         # StreamSource, StreamConfig types
      config/         # App config types
    shared/
      ui/             # Reusable UI components
      hooks/          # Shared hooks (useAnimationFrame, etc.)
      lib/            # Utility functions
      styles/         # Design tokens (main.css)
    workers/          # OffscreenCanvas + telemetry workers
    services/         # WebSocket, StreamManager, PerformanceMonitor
  ```
- Each feature has internal: `components/`, `hooks/`, `stores/`, `types.ts`
- Barrel exports (`index.ts`) for each module

## Steps
1. Create all directories
2. Create placeholder index.ts files
3. Create feature-internal structure for video, hud, telemetry, touch, debug
